      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Of the two vitamins A and C, one is hydrophilic and water-soluble while the other is hydrophobic and fat-soluble. Which is which?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbGNRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--9a6daca5f5a2e868e805ebf59c0acb56644f37c2/OChem_02_12_005.jpg\" alt=\"The bond-line structures of vitamin A (retinol) and vitamin C (ascorbic acid).\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "Vitamin C is water-soluble (hydrophilic); vitamin A is fat-soluble (hydrophobic)."
        }
      ],
      "community_solutions": []
    }
  ],
